text: Moskovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Moskovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 1,879 as of 2010. There are 21 streets. == Geography == It is located 25 km from Dyurtyuli. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Moskovo
